<h2 id="head-c8eea1b80ba437eb2c7d9d8e4a7a1c0c36ddce4e">Bugs</h2>
Report any bugs here <h2 id="head-fce06e20e5f7f74aacccab40b59b75a56c8f7305">Comments</h2>
Christopher: Love the corpse master! I might 'borrow' that idea for my own mod (ToME and 1/2) if that's okay with you. <p>
<strong><a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a></strong>: Sure thing, go ahead. My original idea was to limit that class to humanoid corpses only, but I don't think we can do that. 
</p>
<h2 id="head-861edba00547bc9ce7a08df78d4378766418179f">Suggestions</h2>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Subrace or Ability: "Thunderkitty", probably akin to berserker. You know... where your cat freaks out and runs around and bounces of the walls/etc with his tail all fluffed out, then 5 minutes later sits calmly washing his paw, looking at you like "Move along, move along, nothing interesting just happened here....." <p>
<strong><a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a></strong>: LOL, I'm so doing that as soon as I figure out how. I'm gonna go check if the berserk ability is hard-coded or lua-coded. If it's lua, I will just make one for the "Thunderkitty" 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: I thought you might like that! FYI, "Thunderkitty" is my own coined term. I've heard it called FRAP (Frenetic Random Activity Period), too; I forget the exact veterinary term, but IIRC it's a tossback to some sort of hardwired or semi-hardwired feline hunting sort of thing. Anyway, I called it Thunderkitty long before I knew about that, and to me, it is just so much more evocative. <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile4.png" alt=";)" height="15" width="15"> My SO and I use the term regularly regarding my cat: "I saw a really good thunderkitty earlier", or "He looks like he's about ready to thunderkitty, doesn't he??".  
</p>
<p>
If you want a joke monster.... I see you mention tentacle monster. Well, this again goes back to my utterly weird RL cat (and a lot of evil, evil humour which I will *not* repeat here!!!) but basically, in my house, my cat's tail is often referred to as his tentacle. He has this thing where, if you are (say) reclining on a couch, he will lie on the back of the couch and "paff" you...i.e., brush whatever part of you he can reach with his tail. Your face, if possible. Repeatedly. Flip, paff, twitch, twitch, paff.... You get the idea. So perhaps some sort of sessile cat sort of thingy, which can teleport (a la deathmolds) and is attracted by light sources. The attack is paffing. Perhaps over a distance of up to 2 squares. For minor damage and/or sneezing attacks. And if you try to hit it, it suddenly jumps away, claws the heck out of you, or damages your footwear. (And no, I will NOT publicly elaborate on that last one...) 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a></strong>: Hmmm, gonna make an unique out of that and call it "Maylith's Cat" :p As soon as I figure all those strange monster flags, that is. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: LOL! His favorite hideout is the tube (one of those cat-tree things), and he's a large, golden-eyed orange tabby.  
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a></strong>: Hehe, he will be there on the next release. Made it a normal monster tho, so people get him anyway hehe. I just don't know how to do the tail paffing thing... I guess I would have to learn how lua works with monster spells, if it does at all. But I gave him an arrow attack :P 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: That's so cool! <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> Anyway, if you manage to figure it out, he should have a chance to do very serious damage (and disenchantment) to footwear. I'm not trying any modules til I get a win in basic ToME, but I'll definitely give yours a try once I do.  
</p>
<p>
Christopher: Catfolk subrace... 'in the hat' <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile.png" alt=":-)" height="15" width="15"> Seriously though, this mods pretty cool (insert more general praise here). 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a></strong>: Hey thanks! <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15">  I'm working on spells right now. I think I will have to buff up Maylith's cat. I based him on Freesia. So it's a newbie monster. I might give him some more hp tho. If I figure out how to do monster spells on lua, I will do that :p ... Oh, Thanks Christopher. <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15">  Right now I'm having trouble with wand generation... Even tho I didn't let any of my spells become wand spells, it still bugs lua when you enter a stave/wand store... eh... I dunno how to fix it. 
</p>
<p>
Christopher: The wand thing... I had the same problem myself not long ago. The problem is something to do with  the wand numbers or something... anyway try deleting all the .raw files and let the game regenerate them. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Here's a (bad) <a class="external" href=".home.earthlink.net/~mosdc/pix/phot-cinn1-i.gif"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">picture</a> of my cat. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a></strong>: Cute <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> Big tail too, no wonder it's a tentacle :p 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: In that picture, it's slightly poofed, and perspective makes it look a little bigger too, but it's still a big tail. Funny part is, it was my SO who gave it the name 'tentacle'. Before my SO, I always thought of it as a prehensile tail, but somehow 'tentacle' has stuck. <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
